{"id":"d=origam-topic-3996//p=d07595d2c389471f820874541eea030c","tags":{"__document_id":["origam-topic-3996"],"__file_type":["text/plain"],"__file_id":["95b124b629a646f791ca56673d2ad500"],"__file_part":["1ab22e42a5694cec8b9a563281767692"],"__part_n":["2"],"__sect_n":["0"],"source":["origam-community"],"topicId":["3996"],"categoryId":["61"],"url":["https://community.origam.com/t/how-to-upgrade-the-origam-platform/3996"],"title":["How to upgrade the ORIGAM platform"],"imagesFound":["9"],"imagesDescribed":["9"],"imageUrl":["https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/4/4faa5dea9ebf1787d9edf66c0e45107dfc44db63.png","https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/b/b7bf67b215bf2c0508ce3788b948ca940d9adf2a.png","https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/f/f02b0ffa968929478f9ff2510c82bbee222fa1cc.png","https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/e/ecb487367a25ff8bfb90c6f0fe901d0be693c562.png","https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/3/3b65d03aec9eb6c490c2a1fbc80d7188dcc8bd14.png","https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/7/79194a08568b6b2d612dc3ce590ff126db509051.png","https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/f/f9e48f232b6a98bb336dde62bdb791d4323a80ae.png","https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/8/8cddffc3cb295a2aa50589866c7bf56542adc388.png","https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/1/1e4fe47de957be12c8fcd2f2a357c609700d8993.png"]},"payload":{"url":"","schema":"20231218A","file":"content.txt","text":" stable versions, so if you create a new project using the \u201CMaster-latest\u201D build, please upgrade your ORIGAM Server, Architect and application model when a new stable version is released. \n \n   Model upgrade \n The metamodel, often referred to simply as the \u201Cmodel,\u201D contains the content definitions for all XML files that define a project or application and just like anything else the default metamodel evolves over time \u2014 new items are added, and existing items may be changed and so on. \n If you update ORIGAM Server and Architect, they contain the current version of the metamodel. You must then convert your application model to this version of the metamodel to make both versions compatible. This conversion is handled automatically by Architect, which updates your model to the current metamodel version when you first open your project. \n In addition to the model you created, your project also contains at least some system packages such as Root or Security, and when their model changes, your project needs to be updated as well.  ORIGAM Server and Architect need to have system packages that are always up-to-date . \n The model upgrade of all the system packages is done by downloading the  origam-model.zip  file, which you can find in the Assets: \n  \n\n\n[Image: https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/3/3b65d03aec9eb6c490c2a1fbc80d7188dcc8bd14.png]\nDescription: The image displays a list of downloadable assets related to the \u0022Origam Architect\u0022 project. It includes file names and their corresponding sizes: \u0022origam-architect-server.zip\u0022 (19.2 MB), \u0022origam-architect.msi\u0022 (10.2 MB), \u0022origam-model.zip\u0022 (2.16 MB), \u0022origam-scheduler.zip\u0022 (21.3 MB), \u0022origam-server.zip\u0022 (36.3 MB). Additionally, there are options for \u0022Source code (zip)\u0022 and \u0022Source code (tar.gz)\u0022 without specified sizes. Each item appears to have an associated SHA-256 hash for file integrity verification. The context suggests this is a software or development-related repository.\n\n\n  \n This zip file contains the system model packages and the translation folder (l10n): \n  \n\n\n[Image: https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/7/79194a08568b6b2d612dc3ce590ff126db509051.png]\nDescription: The image displays a file directory structure labeled \u0022origam-model,\u0022 with the folder \u0022model\u0022 expanded to show its subfolders. The visible subfolders include \u0022Security,\u0022 \u0022Root Menu,\u0022 \u0022Root,\u0022 \u0022Documentation,\u0022 \u0022Chat,\u0022 \u0022Audit,\u0022 \u0022Attachments,\u0022 and \u0022I10n.\u0022 Each folder is represented with a blue folder icon. The apparent purpose of this structure is to organize various components of a model within the Origam framework.\n\n\n  \n \n   The safest way to do this is to delete the files of all the system packages used in your project model (at least Security and Root) and then copy the new version. \n \n Changes can also occur at the data level, so the update may include deployment scripts that modify the database structure (new table or field), data content of system packages or functions (new application role) or it can include even a new database procedure. ORIGAM Architect will also take care of running these scripts automatically when you first open your project. \n When you open your project in a newer version of Architect, all the updates will happen automatically once you load any of the affected packages. However, if you try to load your model in an older version of Architect, it will be rejected. If no changes have occurred in the metamodel between two specific Architect versions, this will not be an issue. \n   Before you start \n Upgrading a platform can be a complex process that can affect both your project model (system packages) and its database (structure, content, and procedural functions), so it is good practice to create a good recovery point in case something goes wrong. Yes, we mean good old backups   \n What to back up before upgrading: \n 1. Model \u2013 save the \u201Cpre-upgrade\u201D version to both local and remote Git repositories. \n 2. Database \u2013 make a backup (\u201Cdump\u201D) of the project database, including both structure and data. \n 3. Custom component data \u2013 builds and plugins for both frontend and backend. \n   Project upgrade \n To open projects created in older versions of Architect in a new version after upgrading, you need to copy the  OrigamSettings.config  file from the old Architect folder to the new one. \n For example, if you upgraded from version 2025.1 to 2025.3 and you are using MS Windows, copy the file  OrigamSettings.","vector_provider":"AI.Ollama.OllamaTextEmbeddingGenerator","vector_generator":"__","last_update":"2026-05-01T23:54:36"},"vector":[-0.012065727,-0.03559092,-0.04615741,0.0032575768,0.01724659,-0.06673268,0.004858515,-0.0011845117,-0.006899434,-0.011750615,0.0038776097,-0.023650415,-0.037613768,0.027980387,0.0021458208,-0.0266522,0.009529333,0.041782934,0.042518627,0.0047564204,-0.009158824,-0.028447937,0.04423219,0.01773456,-0.0058406885,0.028258221,-0.04392923,-0.0054005217,0.010036857,0.050322182,-0.0020736123,-0.036481515,-0.022026472,0.0048272596,-0.0067483005,-0.003279202,0.03342856,-0.022285413,-0.0337698,0.029151674,-0.0034864154,-0.016185727,-0.011202887,0.0033404308,-0.00013841037,-0.064480595,0.01566233,0.0022447733,0.028877677,-0.047458533,-0.01019259,-0.0339511,0.0021983583,-0.033972535,0.033427224,0.052576415,-0.06270907,-0.023709027,-0.06996237,0.03189633,-0.026650313,0.012971635,0.0032435206,-0.03478473,-0.008164752,0.02432993,-0.00949686,0.009838746,-0.02823452,-0.03664939,-0.007144297,-0.019001141,-0.06526554,-0.03990236,-0.03629359,0.02471365,0.0138082905,-0.003396393,-0.041001372,0.022089906,-0.008234367,-0.00012689603,0.011960555,0.00065712223,-0.03577172,-0.0048254947,-0.03505131,0.05077654,0.024646193,0.0610312,-0.01836876,-0.03321081,0.04468655,-0.07101041,-0.014999632,-0.0024899528,0.010935747,-0.0021561687,0.029884856,0.00089893333,-0.002011258,-0.0708209,-0.057033576,0.019578464,-0.007043086,-0.01325564,0.0038350048,-0.011386622,-0.025041018,-0.037503283,0.008892484,-0.000115391114,0.005822838,-0.020333856,-0.019521808,-0.04007246,0.00048174954,-0.052102804,-0.0010465857,0.0013504254,-0.03291681,0.0023715817,0.105521694,-0.020575577,-0.011361923,-0.005406781